laboratory_examinations.findings: Potassium level is 6.7 mEq/L, which is outside the normal range (ref range 3.5-5.3 mEq/L).

Liver normal echogenicity, no focal hepatic lesions, normal common bile duct (2 mm), gallbladder mildly distended with cholelithiasis (large impacted gallstone 1.5 cm in neck, smaller mobile 6-mm stone), gallbladder wall normal thickness, no pericholecystic fluid.
